Working fine after this change. 
```
@Configuration
public class RetryConfig {
    @Bean
    public RetryConfiguration retryConfiguration() {
        return new RetryConfiguration();
    }
}
```

Remove the `@Bean` for the `RetryConfiguration`, the same configuration class is already automatically imported when you add [`@EnableRetry`][1]. Hence doubling the configuration. 

```java
@Configuration
@EnableRetry
public class RetryConfig { }
```

When you have both the annotation and the `@Bean` method you get a double proxy/interceptor for the retry logic. Each interceptor will do the configured number of retries, however the inner one will do the configured number of retries each time it gets called. 

So when the retry count is 2, the outer interceptor will call the inner interceptor twice, which will fail only after executing each call twice as well. Now when increasing the number to 3 it the outer will, eventually, call the inner interceptor 3 times, which on each call will execute 3 retries as well. 

[1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring-retry/docs/api/current/org/springframework/retry/annotation/EnableRetry.html
